## Decorator with Parameters

::: {#8620ab2a .cell execution_count=9}
``` {.python .cell-code}
def your_decorator(func):
  def wrapper(*args,**kwargs):
    # Do stuff before func...
    print("Before func!") 
    func(*args,**kwargs)
    # Do stuff after func...
    print("After func!")
  return wrapper

@your_decorator
def foo(bar):
  print("My name is " + bar)

foo("Jack")
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Before func!
My name is Jack
After func!
```
:::
:::


## Decorator Template

```python
import functools

def your_decorator(func):
  @functools.wraps(func) # For preserving the metadata of func.
  def wrapper(*args,**kwargs):
    # Do stuff before func...
    result = func(*args,**kwargs)
    # Do stuff after func..
    return result
  return wrapper
```
